ZH: 这个苹果已经开始腐烂了。
EN: This apple has started to rot.

ZH: 这块肉闻起来有点腐烂。
EN: This piece of meat smells a bit rotten.

ZH: 这些废物经过几个星期后会开始腐烂。
EN: These waste materials will start to decay after a few weeks.

ZH: 小鱼船上腐烂的味道令人作呕。
EN: The stench of rotting fish on the boat is nauseating.

ZH: 没有及时清理的厨余会腐烂产生有害气体。
EN: Kitchen waste that is not cleared in time will decay and produce harmful gases.

ZH: 遇到腐烂的食物，要及时清理，以免滋生细菌。
EN: When encountering rotten food, clean it up in time to prevent bacteria growth.

ZH: 处理腐烂的植物部分可以用于堆肥。
EN: Rotting plant parts can be used for compost.

ZH: 垃圾分类能够减少塑料等材料的腐烂速度。
EN: Waste sorting can reduce the speed of decay for materials like plastic.

ZH: 环境温度和湿度会影响腐烂的速度。
EN: The temperature and humidity of the environment will affect the speed of decay.

ZH: 腐烂的动物尸体会引来飞蝇和其他害虫。
EN: Rotting animal corpses attract flies and other pests.

ZH: 墙角长时间积蓄的湿气会导致木材腐烂。
EN: Moisture accumulating in the corners of walls for a long time can lead to wood rot.

ZH: 地下室的潮湿环境容易导致纸张腐烂。
EN: The damp environment in the basement is prone to causing paper to rot.

ZH: 腐烂的果皮会被细菌污染。
EN: Rotting fruit peel can be contaminated by bacteria.

ZH: 煤渣在阳光下很容易腐烂。
EN: Coal slag is easily prone to decay in sunlight.

ZH: 青草掺杂着腐烂的叶子和树枝。
EN: The grass is mixed with rotting leaves and branches.

ZH: 沼泽地是很容易发生植物腐烂的地方。
EN: The swamp is a place where plants decay easily.

ZH: 实验室里用于观察腐烂过程的设备。
EN: Equipment in the laboratory for observing the process of decay.

ZH: 气候对果实腐烂的速度有很大影响。
EN: The climate has a great influence on the speed of fruit decay.

ZH: 通过处理垃圾可以减少环境中的腐烂物。
EN: Handling garbage can reduce the amount of rot in the environment.
